<br>
Banish pet, keep bracer/arm dot on him(free damage = nice) melee away at him, and heal when he lifetaps, dispell/cure all dots. lifetap generally works like half a nuke, half a heal for the same mana, so unless he is taking damage from nukes, it aint very effecient. not compared to our heal.<br>
<br>
oom necro = dead necro.<br>
<br>
60 druid vs 59/60 wizard.<br>
<br>
Heal till he runs oom, melee him, and keep bracer/arm Dot on him.<br>
<br>
oom wizard = dead wizard.<br>
<br>
...<br>
<br>
General advise would be to keep fire, cold and magic ressistance up against the wizard, and overall keep your manapool as large as possible.<br>
<br>
Magic(enough to keep ya from getting snared) ressistance vs the necro. pr and dr is ok to have high too, but remember, cure is 50mana, and his dot is probably 450 or so mana.<br>
keep manapool as large as possible.<br>
<br>
none of these two classes can melee worth @#%$, so when they are oom, they are dead.<br>
<br>
Against the bard...<br>
<br>
if he knows his @#%$ you are dead, if he doesnt, he will die from a winged death or two =x<br>
<br>
Good luck!<br>
<br>
